data.description: This spacious 3 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom home with attached 2 Car Garage is located in a quiet Port Charlotte neighborhood yet is minutes from all amenities. NO HOA. This light and bright home features an open and split bedroom floor plan with Living Room, separate Dining Room, well equipped Kitchen, Inside Laundry with washer and dryer, Family Room and huge screened Lanai. Both the Dining Room and Living Room at the front of the house have large windows offering lots of natural light. The Kitchen features white cabinetry, stone counters, breakfast bar, pantry closet and stainless appliances. The Kitchen opens to the large Family room with vaulted ceiling, wood laminate flooring and Lanai access. The Master Bedroom suite features a deep walk in closet and private bathroom with dual sinks, soaking tub and walk in shower. There are two additional generous sized bedrooms with double closets and the guest bathroom has a tub/shower combo. Your living space extends to the 48x16 screened Lanai where you can enjoy the fabulous Florida weather. Other features include vaulted ceilings, wood laminate in the living areas and carpet in the bedrooms, hurricane shutters and impact glass windows, sliding screen doors at the garage entrance.  ***NEW impact glass windows July 2022.....NEW A/C June 2023....NEW ROOF 2023....Brand NEW EXTERIOR PAINT 2023....NEW lanai screens 2023****  FURNITURE IS NEGOTIABLE. Utilities are county water and septic. *Home is 14 feet above sea level per seller* This home is just blocks from shopping, dining, medical care, entertainment. Minutes from the Charlotte Sports Park and 10 minutes to the Port Charlotte Beach Complex - a beach park with a community pool, tennis courts, bocce courts, basketball courts, playground, volleyball court, boat ramp, kayak launch, fishing pier and 6000SF recreation center. An easy drive to gorgeous Gulf beaches in Englewood and Manasota Key and world class fishing on Boca Grande. This home is perfect for a family or those expecting lots of winter visitors!
